{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Vegetables","content":["Place water in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket, weigh in potatoes then cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 4<b>. Meanwhile, place cauliflower in Varoma dish.","Place covered Varoma into position and steam <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma and transfer cauliflower to a baking dish.","Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer potatoes to baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Discard cooking water.","Preheat oven to 200°C."]},{"title":"Béchamel","content":["Place Gruyère in mixing bowl and grate <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter, flour, mustard (if using), salt and pepper then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add milk and cook <b>7 min\/90°C\/speed 3<b>.","Distribute haddock pieces over potatoes and cauliflower, pour over béchamel, stir gently with spatula to coat all the ingredients, then sprinkle over reserved grated cheese. Bake for 20-25 minutes (200°C) until golden brown and bubbling.","Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Vegetables","content":["1000 g water","350 g potatoes, peeled, cut in pieces (2 cm)","1 cauliflower, medium (approx. 600 g), cut in bite-sized florets","2 pinches fine sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper"]},{"title":"Béchamel","content":["80 g Gruyère cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","5 g fresh parsley leaves","40 g unsalted butter, diced","40 g plain flour","1 Tbsp wholegrain mustard              (optional)","¼ fine sea salt, or to taste","¼ ground black pepper, or to taste","550 g milk","500 g smoked haddock, skinless, cut in pieces (3-4 cm)"]}],"id":"r294692","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-KzWwbQRwPm4\/XZWYeCfQb4I\/AAAAAAAAd-k\/1Wetivv49qIYL1AXjAj87C8Bx_XO2VUhACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Av3ZA4_IUzG1Jc0E.png","title":"Smoked Haddock and Cauliflower Bake","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"26.2 g","fat":"10.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27.3 g","calories":"1329 kJ \/ 316 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This delicious all-in-one dinner cooks fish, potatoes and vegetables together in a creamy béchamel sauce. Steaming the cauliflower and potatoes in the Varoma first means the haddock can be added just before going into the oven, resulting in tender, flaky pieces of fish. A tasty and comforting meal to enjoy with family or friends."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","55m","6 portions"]}